## When to use
Use this skill when you need to quickly identify which processes are consuming the most CPU resources on your Linux machine.

## Approach
Utilize the shell_exec tool to run the `ps` command with options `-eo pid,ppid,cmd,%cpu,%mem --sort=-%cpu` to list and sort all running processes by their CPU usage in descending order. This provides an easy way to monitor system load and identify potential performance bottlenecks.

## Example
```
shell_exec("ps -eo pid,ppid,cmd,%cpu,%mem --sort=-%cpu")
```

## Pitfalls
- Ensure the `ps` command is available on your system.
- The `-eo` option might vary depending on your version of `ps`, use `-o` if necessary.